<treatment><number>1a.</number><TaxonIdentification Status="ACCEPTED"><genus_name>Dianthus</genus_name><species_name>armeria</species_name><species_authority>Linnaeus</species_authority><subspecies_name>armeria</subspecies_name></TaxonIdentification><description>Plants annual or biennial. Stems erect, simple or branched, 4–88 cm, often pubescent. Leaves: sheath 1–4 mm, 1–2 times as long as stem diam.; blade linear to narrowly oblanceolate, 2–10.5 cm, green, margins basally ciliate. Inflorescences usually open 3–6-flowered cymes or flowers some-times solitary; bracts linear, equaling or longer than calyx, herbaceous, apex acute; bracteoles 4, green, linear to lanceolate, 3/4–1 times as long as calyx, herbaceous, apex acute. Pedicels 0.1–3 mm. Flowers subsessile; calyx 20–25-veined, 11–20 mm, pubescent, lobes acuminate, 2–7 mm; petals reddish with white dots (rarely all white), bearded, 3–8(–10) mm, apex dentate. Capsules 10–16 mm, slightly shorter than calyx. Seeds 1.1–1.4 mm. 2n = 30 (Europe).</description><phenology>spring</phenology><phenology>mar</phenology><phenology>apr</phenology><phenology>may</phenology><phenology>summer</phenology><phenology>jun</phenology><phenology>jul</phenology><phenology>aug</phenology><habitat>roadsides</habitat><habitat>fields</habitat><habitat>shores</habitat><habitat>open woods</habitat><habitat>waste places</habitat><elevation>0–2300 m;</elevation><introduced>introduced;</introduced><ca_distribution>Alta.</ca_distribution><ca_distribution>B.C.</ca_distribution><ca_distribution>N.B.</ca_distribution><ca_distribution>N.S.</ca_distribution><ca_distribution>Ont.</ca_distribution><ca_distribution>P.E.I.</ca_distribution><ca_distribution>Que.</ca_distribution><us_distribution>Ala.</us_distribution><us_distribution>Ariz.</us_distribution><us_distribution>Ark.</us_distribution><us_distribution>Calif.</us_distribution><us_distribution>Colo.</us_distribution><us_distribution>Conn.</us_distribution><us_distribution>Del.</us_distribution><us_